A. D. REYNOLDS, Jr., v. COMMISSIONER OF INTERNAL REVENUE. No. 6956. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. Oct. 7, 1936. Woodward, Dawson & Hobson, of Louisville, Ky., for petitioner. Robert H. Jackson, Asst. Atty. Gen., for respondent.

Before HICKS, SIMONS, and ALLEN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

It is ordered that the appeal herein be and the same is dismissed pursuant to motion of appellant.
